en and Russell have both graduated into official Doctors and are, I think, running a small GP (General Poetry) practice just outside of Glasgow, while we three others are slogging away in second year.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":2062},"end":{"line":10,"column":583,"offset":2644}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":2062},"end":{"line":10,"column":583,"offset":2644}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5cb8ecfa4d6ae8d4689c1a41a92067ba/22492/pg-postersmall.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 141.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"reading deets (poster designed by Richard Hanrahan)\"\n        title=\"reading deets (poster designed by Richard Hanrahan)\"\n        src=\"/static/5cb8ecfa4d6ae8d4689c1a41a92067ba/4b190/pg-postersmall.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5cb8ecfa4d6ae8d4689c1a41a92067ba/e07e9/pg-postersmall.jpg 200w,\n/static/5cb8ecfa4d6ae8d4689c1a41a92067ba/066f9/pg-postersmall.jpg 400w,\n/static/5cb8ecfa4d6ae8d4689c1a41a92067ba/4b190/pg-postersmall.jpg 800w,\n/static/5cb8ecfa4d6ae8d4689c1a41a92067ba/22492/pg-postersmall.jpg 818w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":2646},"end":{"line":12,"column":99,"offset":2744}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"reading deets (poster designed by ","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":100,"offset":2745},"end":{"line":12,"column":134,"offset":2779}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.richardhanrahan.co.uk"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Richard Hanrahan","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":135,"offset":2780},"end":{"line":12,"column":151,"offset":2796}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":134,"offset":2779},"end":{"line":12,"column":187,"offset":2832}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":99,"offset":2744},"end":{"line":12,"column":188,"offset":2833}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":2646},"end":{"line":12,"column":188,"offset":2833}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I’ve been doing quite a lot of editing this week, in preparation for said readings/sending things away to magazines because ain’t nobody gonna come knocking on my door with a publishing deal amiright? I’ve mentioned before that I am ridiculously lazy/nervous/picky about putting my work out there and I think it’s because of this editing process. Sometimes I discover old poems that I wrote years ago and filed under “Fucking Dire Never Read Again” and realise they’re not actually that bad after a few tweaks, but most of the time I wind up editing myself into a corner clutching words like “darkness” and “blood” and “eggs” and insisting I can squeeze them into every single poem if I just keep cutting and pasting. It becomes very boring very quickly and I only have myself to blame. I’m really working on an objective point of view for editing but it’s haaaaaard.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":2835},"end":{"line":14,"column":868,"offset":3702}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":2835},"end":{"line":14,"column":868,"offset":3702}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I am, however, finding it so useful to workshop pretty much everything I write with Poetry Gang (did I mention we’re doing a reading this week? Click ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":3704},"end":{"line":16,"column":151,"offset":3854}}},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.facebook.com/events/1734610713429122/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"here","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":152,"offset":3855},"end":{"line":16,"column":156,"offset":3859}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":151,"offset":3854},"end":{"line":16,"column":208,"offset":3911}}},{"type":"text","value":" for more info). We meet just about every week and share thoughts on one another’s work. Having four voices of reason critiquing my writing in a friendly environment definitely helps to put stuff in perspective – you may have gathered, I can get really surreal really quickly if I’m not kept in check.","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":208,"offset":3911},"end":{"line":16,"column":509,"offset":4212}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":3704},"end":{"line":16,"column":509,"offset":4212}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Anyway, I’ve spent bloody ages intermittently writing this, singing along to the Les Misérables soundtrack and refreshing my hot water bottle so I should really get back to some actual work. Here’s a round-up of my week:","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":4214},"end":{"line":18,"column":221,"offset":4434}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1,"offset":4214},"end":{"line":18,"column":221,"offset":4434}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type"