out for Tony Harrison and tap into my Yorkshire upbringing. Elsewhere, I wrote TWO sonnets. Well one and a half…but I’m counting it.","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":12,"offset":4612},"end":{"line":22,"column":257,"offset":4857}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1,"offset":4601},"end":{"line":22,"column":257,"offset":4857}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Exercise:","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":3,"offset":4861},"end":{"line":24,"column":12,"offset":4870}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1,"offset":4859},"end":{"line":24,"column":14,"offset":4872}}},{"type":"text","value":" Nice dose of swimmer’s ear means no swimming this week, sad faces all round. Loads of walking and yoga instead though.","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":14,"offset":4872},"end":{"line":24,"column":133,"offset":4991}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1,"offset":4859},"end":{"line":24,"column":133,"offset":4991}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Puppy:","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":3,"offset":4995},"end":{"line":26,"column":9,"offset":5001}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1,"offset":4993},"end":{"line":26,"column":11,"offset":5003}}},{"type":"text","value":" Still super cute and virtually a real dog now, so will probably stop having to call him a puppy. Read something about a dog who died and cried loads and hugged him for about an hour.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":11,"offset":5003},"end":{"line":26,"column":194,"offset":5186}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1,"offset":4993},"end":{"line":26,"column":194,"offset":5186}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"typ